Section: libs
Homepage: https://github.com/ryancornish/sigctx
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: libsigctx1
Architecture: amd64
Multi-Arch: same
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: resume rt_sigreturn-compatible CPU contexts (runtime library)
 sigctx builds signal-frame-shaped CPU contexts that the Linux kernel accepts
 on the rt_sigreturn syscall. That is the primitive underneath cooperative or
 preemptive userspace thread switching on x86-64, used by runtimes and green
 thread schedulers.
 .
 This package contains the shared library.

Package: libsigctx-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: amd64
Multi-Arch: same
Depends: libsigctx1 (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: resume rt_sigreturn-compatible CPU contexts (development files)
 sigctx builds signal-frame-shaped CPU contexts that the Linux kernel accepts
 on the rt_sigreturn syscall. That is the primitive underneath cooperative or
 preemptive userspace thread switching on x86-64, used by runtimes and green
 thread schedulers.
 .
 This package contains the headers, the development symlink, the pkg-config
 file, and the CMake package configuration.
